---
description: Require plan-first behavior for security-sensitive and contract-sensitive changes.
alwaysApply: true
---
- Use plan mode before changing auth middleware behavior; public endpoint shape (`/mcp`, `/healthz`); MCP tool names or JSON schemas; memory, status, or sensitivity enums; vault layout or file naming rules; compatibility wrapper response shapes; or any behavior that broadens automatic writes or weakens access control.
- Use plan mode before changing markdown-first persistence flow, vault-path conventions, or markdown to SQLite synchronization behavior.
- For complex work, separate plan, implementation, and verification.
- Run the smallest relevant check first.
- Do not claim completion when verification is still manual or unconfirmed.
